The Borough of Hanover Municipal Water Works Filter Plant Accidental Release Prevention Program is based upon the following elements:

1.    High level of training for the operators;

2.    Preventative maintenance program for equipment;

3.    Use of modern process and safety equipment;

4.    Use of accurate and effective standard operating procedures, written with the participation of the operators;

5.    Performance of a Hazard Review of the equipment and procedures; and

6.    Implementation of an auditing and inspection program.

Chemical specific prevention steps include availability of self contained breathing apparatus (SCBA), awareness of the hazards and toxic properties of chlorine, and the presence of a chlorine gas detector connected to an alarm and telephone dialer.

    Based on available information, there has not been an accidental release of chlorine in more than 35 years. Therefore, there have been no accidental releases of chlorine within the 5 year review period.

